# Brain workspace (`~/brain`)

This folder is Abhishek’s **Personal Knowledge Accelerator**: structured markdown in `knowledge/`, query index in `data/brain.db`, inbox in `inbox/`, agents and skills under `.claude/`.

## Single source of truth

Before doing substantive brain, PM, or sync work, align with:

- `.claude/CLAUDE.md` — taxonomy, frontmatter, SQLite patterns, MCP expectations, invariants
- `AGENTS.md` — short index of agents and slash-command skills

## Agents (via Task tool)

| Agent | Role |
| --- | --- |
| **Sorter** | Inbox orchestration and classification |
| **Keeper** | Write and index knowledge; answer lookups |
| **Scout** | Pull Jira, Confluence, GitHub into `knowledge/` |

## Skills

When the user’s request matches a skill’s description, **read that skill’s `SKILL.md` and follow it**. Skills live in `.claude/skills/<name>/` and are also linked from `~/.claude/skills/` for Claude Code.

Triggers include: plan a feature, write a PRD, user story, code review, ship, investigate, sync Jira/Confluence, ops feedback/bug, weekly email, discovery framing.

## Invariants (do not ignore)

1. **Markdown is truth** — SQLite is for search; do not delete knowledge markdown casually; update in place.
2. **Frontmatter** on knowledge items: at least `title`, `category`, `tags`, `created`, `updated` per `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.
3. **Query the index first** for context-heavy tasks: `sqlite3 ~/brain/data/brain.db "<query>"` (see `.claude/CLAUDE.md` for examples).

## User-level Cursor

Global rules may live in `~/.cursor/rules/` (e.g. Databricks read-only). This project rule applies when the workspace is `~/brain`.
